{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01JqV5UkQEmyU6vNPx8w6ERG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a thorough understanding of all three failures, the history, and the code. Here's my analysis before writing the plan:\n\n**Failure 1 (KREM SELEROWY → UuIw):** Two bugs. Bug A: `/ Jesien / Zupy` is a breadcrumb with multiple `/` separators, but it passes hard filters and triggers false bilingual suppression of the real title. Fix: filter lines with 2+ `/` chars as breadcrumbs (safe — merged continuation lines like SAFFRON only have 1 `/`). Bug B: `UuIw` has 4 letters escaping the ≤3 threshold. Fix: detect mid-word casing transitions (`[a-z][A-Z]`) as garbled — no natural language has this.\n\n**Failure 2 (LABANEH → BALLS):** `MAKES 25 LABANEH` is correctly filtered as metadata, but `BALLS` on the next line is orphaned and enters the pool. It then destroys the correctly merged title via \"shorter wins\" dedup. Fix: metadata continuation suppression — when a metadata line is filtered, also suppress the immediately following line if it's a short (≤1 word) ALL_CAPS fragment.\n\n**Failure 3 (Smażona zielona fasolka → DLA & OSOB):** OCR corrupted `4` → `&`, defeating `/^DLA\\s+\\d/i`. Fix: expand the pattern to also match `DLA` + any token + `OSOB`/`OSÓB` serving-size words, making it OCR-resilient."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6071,"cache_read_input_tokens":53363,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6071},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"beba072c-8756-4212-892f-70153dbd85fa","uuid":"71095b1e-a248-41ac-95aa-8a989f931617"}
